<br>
We all agree we don't want any clique forming or any elitism.  I think we all agree that every 6 months mod should be evaluated based on their needs, the needs of the posters and the needs of the board in general.<br>
<br>
I agree that if a mod is doing a good job they should not be punished by being removed, yet it does open up  a whole process that I think might not be productive in the long run.  One person in the community with a big voice can skew the discussion to make a moderator feel thery are not doing a good job when in fact they are and visa versa.  All of these thigns can hurt a person.  And if we decide ahead of time what the 6 month review will be, no one can be hurt, because it will be expected.  This ultimately gives us structure and it will make it easier to run the board.<br>
<br>
Here is the thing, in the end we want diversity and we want there to be some structure that everyone can count on AND we dont' want the Admins to change the rules in the middle.  (Now do we?? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  We want it to be an easy transition at the 6 month mark and we want people to all agree on what will happen in 6 months.<br>
<br>
So here is my proposal (and thank you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Senar</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> your thoughts helped quite a bit)<br>
<br>
Mod's will come up for review every 6 months.  Said review will consist of this, (if we all agree with my proposal).. <br>
<br>
1.  Does the Mod want to still moderate? <br>
2.  Did the forum and the community propser while a moderator was in charge? <br>
<br>
If the answers to these two questions are Yes, the moderator will be given the choice of taking a new assignment in a different forum or taking a break from Mod'ing for 6 months.<br>
<br>
During a break, they will be on reserve status and will/can fill in if a moderator needs to take any extended time off.  A subsitute Moderator if you will.<br>
<br>
If a moderator no longer wishes to moderate at all, they can step down and/or be added to the reserve list, whatever their decision is.<br>
<br>
If the Admins remove a Moderator for 'cause' the moderator must wait for 6 months before being considered to be re-instated.  And the whole board must apporve.  <br>
<br>
For cause is defiened as this:  Gross violation of Board Policy, that caused real upset to the community and/or put the board at risk.  <br>
<br>
(Real upset is NOT defined as a few posters upset over a thread or a mod action.. It MUST relate to BOARD POLICY BEING VIOLATED.)<br>
<br>
Mod's who wish to rotate to a different forum will be put before that forum (Exactly as they were this time) for discussion.<br>
<br>
Mod's who wish to take a break will be on Reserve.<br>
<br>
Poster's who wish to become Mod's will post there wishes in the disucssion threads at the time.<br>
<br>
What do you think?? <br>
<br>
And I promise to get something up on warnings and such by Saturday folks. Thanks for hanging in there until then.. and thanks to the whole membership for being so nice and waiting..<br>
<br>
~ Cait<br>
<br>
